# Unused Chapters Feature

Auto-save chapters containing unused items + Delete button to clean up after script completion.

## Proposed Changes

### UI — Unused Chapters Folder Selector + Delete Button

#### [MODIFY] [rewrite_style_tab.py](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py)

**1. Add folder path widget** (near output folder selector):
- TextInput `_txt_unused_dir` + Browse button
- Default empty — user picks folder once, remembered via save/restore config

**2. Add Delete button**:
- Red/orange color (`background: #e74c3c`) — visually distinct
- State-dependent popup:
  - No folder set → *"Chưa chọn thư mục unused chapters"*
  - Pipeline not run yet → *"Chưa hoàn thành kịch bản — không có file để xoá"*
  - Folder empty → *"Thư mục rỗng — không có file để xoá"*
  - Has files → *"Xoá {N} file trong {folder}? Không thể hoàn tác."* + confirm/cancel

---

### Pipeline — Auto-Copy Unused Chapter Files

#### [MODIFY] [rewrite_style_tab.py](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py)

After outline selects products (line ~2258), add step:

```
all_products = {p["product_name"] for p in blueprint["product_evaluation"]}
selected_products = {names from outline chapters}
unused_products = all_products - selected_products

If unused_products AND unused_dir is set:
  For each source chapter file:
    If chapter text mentions any unused product name:
      Copy file → unused_dir (skip if same name already exists, add _2 suffix)
  Log: "✓ Copied {N} unused chapters to {folder}"
```

**Works for both merge and single-folder**: any time the outline uses fewer items than the blueprint contains.

---

### Source Tracking — Map Products to Chapter Files

The input text tags each chapter: `=== PART {i}: {filename} ===`. Need to map unused `product_name` → source chapter file:

- Option A: **Text matching** — search each chapter text for product name → simple, ~95% accurate
- Option B: **Add `source_parts` to blueprint prompt** — AI tags which PART each product came from → more accurate but modifies blueprint schema

**Chosen: Option A** (simple, no prompt changes needed). Fallback: if a product can't be matched to any single chapter, skip it (don't copy).

## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing
- Run pipeline with 10 items, chapter_range set to 7-8
- Verify ~2-3 chapters copied to unused folder
- Click Delete button → verify popup + deletion
- Re-run → verify new unused files added without overwriting
